HEADWORD: Lernæacea
<hw>Ler`n⟦ae⟧*a"ce*a</hw>
<pr>(l⟦etil⟧r`n⟦esl⟧*⟦amac⟧"sh⟦esl⟧*⟦adot⟧)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>
<ety>[NL. See <er>Lern⟦ae⟧a</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A
suborder of copepod Crustacea, including a large number of remarkable
forms, mostly parasitic on fishes. The young, however, are active and
swim freely. See <xex>Illustration</xex> in Appendix.</def>⟦br⟧
